      "created_at": "2026-05-26T19:44:31Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-26T20:07:32Z",
      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "> BIP 3: _It is recommended that complicated proposals be split into separate BIPs that each focus on a specific component of the overall proposal._\r\n\r\nI think the complexity and scope of these changes relative to something like Segwit or Taproot (which have multiple associated BIPs) is much more narrow and does not justify a split.\r\n\r\nRegardless, given how far along this BIP is and how long the public discussion has been ongoing, changing the BIP (at what is effectively the 11th hour) this drastically is unreasonable. It seems sensible for a competing proposal to have its own BIP entirely, even if it simply removes or changes a single component of BIP 54. It also allows the community a more clear path towards comparing these proposals. ",
      "user": {
